## Tuberculosis Data\
\
### TB Cases (2003-2011)\
\
**Source**: HealthMap TB  \
**URL**: https://healthmap.org/tb/  \
**Geographic Level**: County (aggregated to CBSA)  \
**Temporal Coverage**: 2003-2011 (primary), with 2006-2010 averages for some states  \
**Format**: CSV with county-level annual case counts\
\
#### Original Data Provider\
State Departments of Public Health contributed data to HealthMap for creation of a public, nationwide TB dataset.\
\
#### Data Description\
- Publicly available TB data from 2006-2010\
- Rates per 100,000 calculated from average number of cases over this timespan\
- Population data from US Census ACS 5-year county estimates, 2006-2010\
\
#### Field Codes\
- **NR** = Not reported\
- **NA** = Not applicable\
\
#### Geographic Reporting Notes\
\
**Standard County-Level Reporting:**\
Most states report at the county level with yearly breakdowns.\
\
**Health District Reporting:**\
The following states report by health district rather than county:\
- **Idaho**: Cases reported by health district; rates calculated using health district population\
- **Mississippi**: Cases reported by health district; rates calculated using health district population\
\
**States with Special Handling:**\
\
| State | Years | Special Considerations |\
|-------|-------|------------------------|\
| Alaska | All | **EXCLUDED** - Cases reported by health district, but no clear geographic link between boroughs and health districts |\
| Missouri | 2007-2011 | Metro areas (Joplin, Kansas City) had cases recorded separately from municipal area. Municipal cases averaged over metro counties and added to independent counts |\
| North Dakota | 2006-2010 | No yearly breakdown available; average cases used |\
| Pennsylvania | 2005-2009 | Different date range than other states |\
| Virginia | All | Combined reporting: Prince William includes Prince William County, Manassas City, Manassas Park City; Fairfax County includes Fairfax City and Falls Church City |\
| Wyoming | 2005-2010 | No yearly breakdown available; average cases used |\
\
#### Data Interpolation Methodology\
\
**Issue**: Some states reported TB cases for certain counties but not all.\
\
**Solution**: Interpolation performed using state totals:\
\
1. Start with total state TB cases\
2. Subtract cases from counties with reported data\
3. Calculate remainder = unreported cases\
4. Divide remainder equally among counties without data\
\
**Example (Nevada 2010)**:\
- Total state cases: 114\
- Clark County: 97 cases\
- Washoe County: 12 cases\
- Carson City: 2 cases\
- **Subtotal reported**: 111 cases\
- **Unreported**: 114 - 111 = 3 cases\
- **Distribution**: 3 cases \'f7 14 remaining counties = 0.214 cases per county (averaged)\
\
#### Data Processing Steps\
\
1. **Import**: County-level TB case data (wide format by year)\
2. **Reshape**: Convert from wide to long format (county-year observations)\
3. **FIPS Assignment**: Create 5-digit county FIPS codes\
4. **Crosswalk Merge**: Join county FIPS to CBSA codes\
5. **Aggregation**: Sum county-level cases to CBSA totals by year\
6. **Rate Calculation**: Calculate TB rate per 100,000 using CBSA population denominators\
