### Air Quality Index (AQI) Summaries (2003-2011)\
\
**Source**: EPA Air Quality Index Report  \
**URLs**: \
- https://www.epa.gov/outdoor-air-quality-data/air-quality-index-report\
- https://aqs.epa.gov/aqsweb/airdata/download_files.html#Annual  \
\
**File Type**: `annual_aqi_by_cbsa_YYYY.zip` (one file per year)  \
**Geographic Level**: CBSA (direct)  \
**Temporal Coverage**: 2000-2023 (subset 2003-2011 used)\
\
#### AQI Metrics\
\
**Day Count Variables**:\
- `dayswith_aqi`: Total days with AQI data\
- `gooddays_aqi`: Days with Good air quality (AQI 0-50)\
- `moderatedays_aqi`: Days with Moderate air quality (AQI 51-100)\
- `unhealthyforsensitivegroupsdays_`: Days Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups (AQI 101-150)\
- `unhealthydays_aqi`: Days Unhealthy (AQI 151-200)\
- `veryunhealthydays_aqi`: Days Very Unhealthy (AQI 201-300)\
- `hazardousdays_aqi`: Days Hazardous (AQI 301+)\
\
**Summary Statistics**:\
- `maxaqi_aqi`: Maximum AQI value for the year\
- `thpercentile_aqi`: 90th percentile AQI (variable name reflects original field)\
- `median_aqi`: Median AQI value\
\
#### EPA AQI Categories\
\
| AQI Range | Category | Color Code | Health Message |\
|-----------|----------|------------|----------------|\
| 0-50 | Good | Green (#00E400) | Air quality is satisfactory |\
| 51-100 | Moderate | Yellow (#FFFF00) | Acceptable; unusually sensitive people should consider limiting prolonged outdoor exertion |\
| 101-150 | Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups | Orange (#FF7E00) | Sensitive groups may experience health effects |\
| 151-200 | Unhealthy | Red (#FF0000) | Everyone may begin to experience health effects |\
| 201-300 | Very Unhealthy | Purple (#8F3F97) | Health alert: everyone may experience more serious health effects |\
| 301+ | Hazardous | Maroon (#7E0023) | Health warnings of emergency conditions |\
