\
**Source**: US Census Bureau Intercensal County Population Estimates  \
**File**: `co-est00int-sexracehisp.csv`  \
**URL**: https://www2.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/datasets/2000-2010/intercensal/county/  \
**Geographic Level**: County  \
**Temporal Coverage**: April 1, 2000 to July 1, 2010\
\
**Variables**:\
- Total population\
- Sex: Male, Female\
- Hispanic Origin: Hispanic, Not Hispanic\
- Race: White, Black, American Indian/Alaska Native (AIAN), Asian, Native Hawaiian/Other Pacific Islander (NHOPI), Two or More Races\
\
**Census Race Codes**:\
- 1 = White alone\
- 2 = Black or African American alone\
- 3 = American Indian and Alaska Native alone\
- 4 = Asian alone\
- 5 = Native Hawaiian and Other Pacific Islander alone\
- 6 = Two or More Races\
\
#### 2011 (Vintage 2011 Estimates)\
\
**Source**: US Census Bureau County Population Estimates  \
**File**: `co-est2011-alldata.csv`  \
**URL**: https://www2.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/datasets/2010-2011/counties/totals/  \
**Geographic Level**: County  \
**Base Date**: April 1, 2010 (Census)  \
**Estimate Date**: July 1, 2011\
\
**Variables**: Same demographic breakdowns as intercensal data\
\
#### Boundary Change Note\
\
**Important**: Intercensal 2003-2010 and 2011 vintage Census boundaries differ slightly.\
\
**Our Approach**:\
- CBSA codes and titles kept consistent across all years\
- Potential boundary changes flagged in data\
- County-to-CBSA aggregation uses crosswalk valid for each time period\
