### Connecticut Planning Region Realignment\
\
**Issue**: Connecticut eliminated county governments and transitioned to planning regions\
\
**Years Affected**: 2003-2011\
\
**Mapping**:\
\
| Old County FIPS | Old County Name | New Planning Region FIPS | Planning Region Name |\
|-----------------|-----------------|--------------------------|----------------------|\
| 09001 | Fairfield County | 09120, 09190 | Greater Bridgeport, Western CT |\
| 09003 | Hartford County | 09110 | Capitol Planning Region |\
| 09005 | Litchfield County | 09160 | Northwest Hills Planning Region |\
| 09007 | Middlesex County | 09130 | Lower CT River Valley Planning Region |\
| 09009 | New Haven County | 09170 | South Central CT Planning Region |\
| 09011 | New London County | 09180 | Southeastern CT Planning Region |\
| 09013 | Tolland County | 09110, 09150 | Capitol, Northeastern |\
| 09015 | Windham County | 09150 | Northeastern CT Planning Region |\
\
**Note**: Some legacy counties map to multiple planning regions\
\
**Processing**:\
1. Original TB/demographic data uses legacy county FIPS\
2. Crosswalk maps old FIPS \uc0\u8594  new planning region FIPS\
3. Planning region FIPS then mapped to CBSA codes\
4. Ensures geographic consistency across 2003-2011\
