## Data Integration Summary\
\
### Final Dataset Structure\
\
**Unit of Analysis**: CBSA-year  \
**Years**: 2003-2011  \
**Number of CBSAs**: Varies by year and data availability (189 CBSAs with complete data)\
\
### Aggregation Methods\
\
| Data Type | Original Level | Aggregation Method |\
|-----------|----------------|-------------------|\
| TB Cases | County | Sum to CBSA |\
| TB Deaths | State | Assign (repeat) to all CBSAs in state |\
| Demographics | County | Sum to CBSA |\
| Air Pollutants | CBSA | Direct (no aggregation) |\
| AQI Metrics | CBSA | Direct (no aggregation) |\
\
### Missing Data Patterns\
\
**By Variable Type**:\
- **TB Cases**: Some CBSAs lack data due to county non-reporting or health district reporting\
- **Air Pollutants**: Not all CBSAs have monitoring stations; coverage varies by pollutant\
- **AQI**: Requires at least one monitoring station; smaller CBSAs may lack coverage\
- **Demographics**: Complete coverage (Census estimates all counties)\
\
**Handling**:\
- Observations with missing outcome or key exposure variables excluded from specific analyses\
- Missing data flags retained for transparency\
- Geographic visualization indicates CBSAs with missing data (gray shading with dashed borders)\
