## Quality Control\
\
### Data Validation Steps\
\
1. **FIPS Code Validation**: All county FIPS verified against Census FIPS standards\
2. **Crosswalk Completeness**: All counties in TB/demographic data matched to CBSA\
3. **Duplicate Detection**: CBSA-year combinations checked for uniqueness\
4. **Range Checks**: Pollutant concentrations and AQI values verified against EPA standards\
5. **Population Denominators**: County populations sum correctly to CBSA totals\
\
### Known Limitations\
\
1. **TB Deaths**: State-level only; no intra-state geographic variation\
2. **Connecticut**: Complex FIPS realignment may introduce minor geographic inconsistencies\
3. **Interpolated TB Cases**: Some county values estimated rather than directly observed\
4. **Air Quality Coverage**: Monitoring station availability creates geographic gaps\
5. **Census Boundaries**: Minor differences between 2003-2010 (intercensal) and 2011 (vintage) estimates\
